{
  "texts": [
    "Specifically, designers can (1) expressively build their prompt to AI with images, colors and semantics;(2) explore connections and themes between visual inspirations by focusing on certain inputs; (3) review and revise prompts interactively before image generation; and (4) appropriate features based on their convergent-divergent needs.The key contributions of this paper include: (1) a preliminary study that investigates how general audiences use GenAI applications for moodboarding resulting in four design implications for designing GenAI for that context; (2) DesignPrompt, a GenAIpowered moodboard tool with designer-centered multimodal input design; and (3) our insights based on a study with 12 professional designers.",
    "We conclude with a discussion and directions for future research in a broader context beyond moodboard.",
    "RELATED WORK 2.1 Creativity Support Tools for Design IdeationCreativity support tools (CSTs) are digital aids \"encompassing one or more creativity-focused features\" [20].",
    "They support different phases in creative processes, with ideation or idea generation being one of the most commonly facilitated stages [14].",
    "Ideation involves generating and developing novel ideas, which is closely related to divergent thinking in creativity research [30]."
  ]
}